function foo(int $a): int { return $a + 1; } function bar(int $b): int { return foo($b) * 2; }  $result = bar(5); echo $result; //Expected output: 12. But if foo function is modified to have an unexpected behavior , like  function foo(int $a): int { if ($a == 5) { return 0; } return $a + 1;} the output will be unexpected 10 instead of 12. This is an example of how unexpected behavior in a function can lead to unexpected behavior in other functions that depend on it. 